Afropop artist Rema’ is set to launch his version of crypto technology, NFT, to connect with his fan base. The Mavin Records/Jonzing World singer made this disclosure during the listening party of his highly anticipated album: ‘Rave & Roses’. He said he would launch an NFT project for fans to have special access to his albums, concerts and build connections. “You all gonna have an NFT. I don’t want my new album just to be for me or my team. I want every ‘Ravers’ to benefit from it. “There is so much going to be tied to the NFT project. For example, you are going to have discount tickets to all my shows, free birthday shout outs and other amazing benefits.”   I’m ahead of Wizkid, Davido, Burna Boy, others –…     Most people on social can’t defend their successes – Shade…     Yomi Casual to wives: don’t transform caring husbands into…   Rema kicked off the year with a release of his infectious melody titled ‘Calm down’ produced by Andre Vibez and London. The single is off his upcoming album. “For me, every phase comes light with every phase becomes a new sound or an advanced state of mind. “So, this song is like the light outside the cave, it’s a sign of hope, strength, and a new beginning,” the 21-year-old pop star said on his trending single. Hinting on his soon-to-be-released album, the ‘Iron man,’ the singer said it would feature International stars including American vocalist Chris Brown, 6lack, AJ Tracey and French singer Yseult. The 15-track body of work is billed for release on March 25, 2022.